Use the standard library
This is how to rounded_avg of n and m:
   Remember that total is sum of n and m
   Remember that avg is quotient of total and 2
   Remember that bits is ""
   When avg is 0, then:
      Remember that bits is "0"
   But, if not:
      Remember that x is avg
      Do this 1000 times:
         When x is 0, then:
            Leave the loop
         End when
         Remember that r is remainder of x and 2
         Remember that digit is sum of r and 48
         Add bits to digit
         Remember that x is quotient of x and 2
      End do
      Remember that bits is reverse of bits
   End when
   The answer is "0b{bits}"
Now you know